title: numberCheck with for loop and mod

content.question: public void numberCheck(int maxNum) { int typeA = 0; int typeB = 0; int typeC = 0; for (int k = 1; k <= maxNum; k++) { if (k % 2 == 0 && k % 5 == 0) typeA++; if (k % 2 == 0) typeB++; if (k % 5 == 0) typeC++; } System.out.println(typeA + " " + typeB + " " + typeC); } What is printed as a result of the call numberCheck(50) ?

skill.text: 3.A: Determine the result or output based on statement execution order in an algorithm.
